--- !u!114 &2050696067516151023
MonoBehaviour:
  m_ObjectHideFlags: 0
  m_CorrespondingSourceObject: {fileID: 0}
  m_PrefabInstance: {fileID: 0}
  m_PrefabAsset: {fileID: 0}
  m_GameObject: {fileID: 6806269699258061759}
  m_Enabled: 1
  m_EditorHideFlags: 0
  m_Script: {fileID: 11500000, guid: f4688fdb7df04437aeb418b961361dc5, type: 3}
  m_Name: 
  m_EditorClassIdentifier: 
  m_Material: {fileID: 0}
  m_Color: {r: 1, g: 1, b: 1, a: 1}
  m_RaycastTarget: 1
  m_RaycastPadding: {x: 0, y: 0, z: 0, w: 0}
  m_Maskable: 1
  m_OnCullStateChanged:
    m_PersistentCalls:
      m_Calls: []
  m_text: "In Physics, inertia is a state of complete equilibrium. Mass is a factor
    of inertia, meaning, the heavier the object is, the more force is required to
    start changing its current state. Moreover, mass is innate inertia, while momentum
    is moving inertia.\n\nIn rotational motion, it is called moment of inertia (sometimes
    called rotational inertia), where it is dependent on both mass and the position
    of the object\u2019s axis. The axis can exist anywhere from within the object
    itself or outside its system. The moment of inertia changes because of the changes
    in position its axis is placed at. By definition, rotational inertia is the resistance
    of a rotating body to change its current state of balance, which in this case,
    is its rotation.\nFORMULA:  i = mr\xB2 where m = mass, and r = radius."
  m_isRightToLeft: 0
  m_fontAsset: {fileID: 11400000, guid: ed9fe41215e4a2c4a9fa581443855244, type: 2}
  m_sharedMaterial: {fileID: -4890204404628985631, guid: ed9fe41215e4a2c4a9fa581443855244, type: 2}
  m_fontSharedMaterials: []
  m_fontMaterial: {fileID: 0}
  m_fontMaterials: []
